@NODE introduction " Primogen Introduction "
@NEXT registering
@{B}@{U}
Introduction
@{UB}@{UU}

Primogen is a tool to help players of the game @{"Jyhad" link Jyhad}.
Primogen  will  help  you  to  keep  track  of  your  favourite Crypts, but more
importanty Primogen will provide valuable statistical and analytical information
about your Crypt.

This  will  help  you  to better understand the strengths and weaknesses of your
crypt  and  thus  help  you to select a more appropriate library.  Primogen will
also  provide  immediate realtime feedback on the effect the addition or removal
of  any  vampires  have on your crypt.

Primogen is Shareware.  Please support the continued development of Primogen and
my bank account by @{"registering" link registering}.

If you do not play Jyhad then you should.

If  you  still  don't play Jyhad, well, then will probably not find this program
useful for anything.  Do feel free to try however.  :)

@ENDNODE 
@NODE Jyhad " What is Jyhad?  "
@{B}@{U}
Overview of Jyhad - An excerpt from the Jyhad rules.  
@{UB}@{UU}

"Jyhad  is  a  collectable  trading card game requiring about 3 hours of playing
time.  In Jyhad two or more players take on the roles of ancient vampires, known
as Methuselahs, engaged in an age-old political battle.  So great and subtle are
the  Methuselahs  that  they are considered mere legend by the younger vampires.
These  younger  vampires think they are pursuing their own ends even as they are
being  used  by  one  Methuselah  to  undercut  the  power base of another.  The
Motivations  for  the  war between the Methuselahs are lost in the sands of dead
civilizations.   Perhaps  the Methuselahs are vying for world conquest.  Perhaps
they  work  under  the  influence of yet older vampires, believing as naively in
their autonomy as do the vampires they control."

Jyhad is based on White Wolf's game @{B}Vampire:The Masquerade.@{UB}

Jyhad is produced by Wizards of the Coast, and is a Trademark of Wizards of the
Coast and White Wolf.  Jyhad was designed by Richard Garfield.

WoTC can be reached @{"here" link contactwotc}.

A Newspaper article I wrote can be found @{"here" link newsarticle}.

Oh... and I almost forgot. Jyhad is being renamed to "Vampire:The Eternal
Struggle".  So if you can't find Jyhad anywhere look for V:TES
