@NODE dupvamp "Duplicate Vampires in the Crypt"
@{B}@{U}
Using Duplicate Vampires in The Crypt
@{UB}@{UU}

This tactis is strongly discouraged, and it should be warned that the currently
Primogen does not accuratly reflect the effects of duplicate vampires in your
crypt.

This tactic  will generally have the following effects.
    - loss of Crypt Speed
    - Increase in Control
    - Decreasing the purity of most disciplines while having minimal if any
      positive effect on the disciplines the duplicate vampires possess.

The only real reason for using this tactic is to increase the probability that
you will be able to get a certain vampire into play.  However there are
drawbacks.  You run the risk of drawing duplicate (and hence useless) vampires
from your crypt.  An additional risk is that if someone puts a vampire (that you
have duplicates of in your deck) into play, a significant portion of your crypt
will become contested.

Putting duplicates of the same vampire in your crypt is generally a bad tactic
and is strongly discouraged.

The current version of Primogen treats all vampires as unique so will give you
misleading results if you include duplicate vampires in your crypt.  A future
version of Primogen will take these considerations into mind.

@ENDNODE

